The paper deals with orientation estimation in 3D, which is a problem commonly encountered in robotics and computer vision. Therefore, cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a new filtering technique that is computationally efficient and suitable for periodic problems, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with nonlinear filtering techniques, which could also fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
